packages.name: zetacomponents/archive
packages.description: The component allows you to create, modify, and extract archive files of  various formats.  The currently supported archives formats are Tar (with  the flavours: ustar, v7, pax, and gnu) and Zip.

packages.name: zetacomponents/authentication
packages.description: The purpose of the Authentication component is to provide support for different means of identification and authentication of users using different providers and protocols.

packages.name: zetacomponents/authentication-database-tiein
packages.description: The purpose of the Authentication component is to provide support for different means of identification and authentication of users using different providers and protocols.

packages.name: zetacomponents/base
packages.description: The Base package provides the basic infrastructure that all packages rely on. Therefore every component relies on this package.

packages.name: zetacomponents/cache
packages.description: A solution for caching, supporting multiple backends allowing you to specify the best performing solution for your caching-problem.

packages.name: zetacomponents/configuration
packages.description: A component that allows you to use configuration files in different formats. The formats include the standard .ini file, and an array based format.

packages.name: zetacomponents/console-tools
packages.description: A set of classes to do different actions with the console (also called shell). It can render a progress bar, tables and a status bar and contains a class for parsing command line options.

packages.name: zetacomponents/database
packages.description: A lightweight database layer on top of PHP's PDO that allows you to utilize a database without having to take care of differences in SQL dialects.

packages.name: zetacomponents/debug
packages.description: This component provides a set of classes that help you to debug an application. It provides timers and report generators for different formats that give a summary of warnings and errors that occurred within your application.

packages.name: zetacomponents/event-log
packages.description: Allows you to log events or audit trails into files or other storage spaces in different formats.

packages.name: zetacomponents/feed
packages.description: This component handles parsing and creating RSS1, RSS2 and ATOM feeds, with support for different feed modules (dc, content, creativeCommons, geo, iTunes).

packages.name: zetacomponents/image-analysis
packages.description: This class allows you to analyse image files in different ways. At least the MIME type of the file is returned. In some cases (JPEG, TIFF and GIF) additional information is gathered as well.

packages.name: zetacomponents/image-conversion
packages.description: A set of classes to apply different filters on images, such as colour changes, resizing and special effects.

packages.name: zetacomponents/mail
packages.description: The component allows you construct and/or parse Mail messages conforming to  the mail standard. It has support for attachments, multipart messages and HTML  mail. It also interfaces with SMTP to send mail or IMAP, POP3 or mbox to  retrieve e-mail.

packages.name: zetacomponents/mvc-authentication-tiein
packages.description: This component provides authentication filters for the MvcTools component.

packages.name: zetacomponents/mvc-tools
packages.description: The MvcTools component provides functionality for request parsing, routing, dispatching, views and response writing. With the tools in this component you can very easily build an MVC framework.

packages.name: zetacomponents/persistent-object
packages.description: This component allows you to store an arbitrary data structures to a fixed database table. The component provides all the functionality needed to fetch, list, delete etc these datastructures.

packages.name: zetacomponents/php-generator
packages.description: Provides a simple interface for creating PHP files and executing PHP code.

packages.name: zetacomponents/signal-slot
packages.description: The SignalSlot component implements a mechanism for inter and intra object communication through the use of signals and slots.

packages.name: zetacomponents/system-information
packages.description: Provides access to common system variables, such as CPU type and speed, and the available amount of memory.

packages.name: zetacomponents/webdav
packages.description: This component allows you to set up and run your own WebDAV (RFC 2518) server, to enable online content editing for the users of your system through the WebDAV HTTP extension.
